-- Rangers Beat Devils 3-0 to Take 2-1 Lead in NHL Playoff Series
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-05-19T19:41:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-19/rangers-beat-devils-3-0-to-take-2-1-lead-in-nhl-playoff-series.html
The  New York  Rangers defeated the  New
Jersey  Devils 3-0 to take a two-games-to-one lead in the
National Hockey League’s Eastern Conference finals.  Dan Girardi and Chris Kreider scored early in the third
period and Ryan Callahan added an empty-net goal to give the
Rangers the victory at the Prudential Center in Newark, New
Jersey.  New York’s Henrik Lunvqvist stopped 36 shots for his NHL-
best third shutout of the playoffs. Martin Brodeur made 19 saves
for New Jersey, which hosts Game 4 in the best-of-seven series
in two days.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  